'''儿童色情旅游'''（{{Lang-en|'''Child Sex Tourism'''}}）是为了参与[[雏妓|儿童性交易]]而进行的一种[[性旅游|性旅游]]，这在商业上促进了[[儿童性虐待|儿童性虐待]]的发生。<ref name=deptstate>{{cite web|url=https://www.state.gov/g/tip/rls/fs/08/112090.htm|title=The Facts About Child Sex Tourism|work=Fact Sheet|publisher=US Dept of State, Office to Monitor and Combat Trafficking in Persons|date=2008-02-29|access-date=2018-07-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090313080604/http://www.state.gov/g/tip/rls/fs/08/112090.htm|archive-date=2009-03-13|dead-url=yes}}</ref> [[联合国|联合国]]《[[儿童权利公约|儿童权利公约]]》里对[[儿童|儿童]]的定义为“所有未满18周岁的人”。<ref name=NewZealand/> 根据[[美国国务院|美国国务院]]的说法，儿童色情旅游会对被剥削的儿童造成身体和精神上的不良后果，这其中可能包括[[性傳染病|性傳染病]]（甚至是[[艾滋病|艾滋病]]）、“[[毒瘾|吸毒成瘾]]、[[怀孕|怀孕]]、[[营养不良|营养不良]]、[[拒绝社交|社交障碍]]，乃至[[死亡|死亡]]”。<ref name=deptstate/> 儿童色情旅游是价值数十亿美元的全球[[性旅游|性旅游]]的一部分，也是[[儿童性剥削|儿童性剥削]]乃至更受到更广泛关注的社会议题——[[雏妓|儿童商业性交易]]的一种形式。儿童色情旅游使得全球每年产生200万名儿童受害者。<ref name=deptstate/><ref name=klain>Klain, ''Prostitution of Children and Child-Sex Tourism: An Analysis of Domestic and International Responses'' 1999, ABA Center on Children and the Law, page 33 cited in {{cite web |url=http://www.yapi.org/rpchildsextourism.pdf |title=Global Child Sex Tourism: Children as Tourist Attractions |author=Susan Song |work=Youth Advocate Program International Resource Paper |publisher=Youth Advocate Program International |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120903204735/http://www.yapi.org/rpchildsextourism.pdf |archivedate=2012-09-03 |accessdate=2010-04-02 }}</ref><ref name=farrell>{{cite news |url=http://www.csmonitor.com/2004/0422/p11s01-wogi.html/ |title=Global campaign to police child sex tourism |author=Michael B. Farrell |date=2004-04-22 |publisher=Christian Science Monitor |accessdate=2010-04-02 |archive-date=2020-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200415040324/https://www.csmonitor.com/2004/0422/p11s01-wogi.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=bacon>{{cite news |url=http://abcnews.go.com/thelaw/Story?id=3385318&page=1 |title=Stolen